The latest data on producer prices shows a slowdown in December compared to the previous month. This is the lowest monthly increase in the Producer Price Index (PPI) since November 2020. The decrease in prices was mainly driven by a reduction in energy and food prices, which are highly volatile. However, there are signs of potential improvement in prices for goods and services related to the supply chain. Despite the economy's recovery, there are still challenges with prices due to supply chain disruptions globally. This report highlights the significance of the Administration's efforts to address supply chain issues and combat the ongoing pandemic.